    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, thank you all for the insights! Now after playing a little I realized the initial question wasn't really the best suited for my case. So, I have this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">inductive</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">zero</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span> <span class=\"n\">arrow</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">infixr</span> <span class=\"bp\">`â†£`</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">50</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">type.arrow</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">pure</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„•</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">type.zero</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">type.zero</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†£</span> <span class=\"n\">pure</span> <span class=\"n\">n</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Can I, for an <code>n : â„•</code>, simply write <code>n</code> to mean <code>pure n</code> in a place where a <code>type</code> is expected? (I realize it's kind of pointless here, but still, out of curiosity)</p>",
